Place a #foil-lined baking sheet{} on a middle rack and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Quarter and peel @red onion{1}(quartered and peeled); finely dice three quarters and thinly slice remaining. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Finely chop @feta cheese{1/2%cup}(finely chopped). Quarter @cremini mushrooms{4%oz}(quartered). Peel and trim @carrots{1}(peeled and trimmed), then finely chop. Thinly slice @Persian cucumber{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon}, half the @ground beef{20%oz}, half the garlic, half the feta, 2 TBSP diced onion, and a couple pinches of @salt{pinches} and @pepper{}. Form into 8 equal-sized meatballs. Drizzle lined #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{2%tsp}. Place meatballs on prepared sheet. Bake until browned and cooked through, about ~{20%minutes}. Remove from oven and cool.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining beef; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Drain off and discard any excess fat. Add mushrooms and carrot to pot. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring, until slightly softened, about ~{5%minutes}.

Add remaining diced onion and remaining garlic to pot. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Add reserved beef, @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz can}, ⅔ cup water, and salt. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low and cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot, until thickened, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to boiling water. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain pasta, then stir into cooked ragù. Turn off heat. Stir in half the @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Divide between plates. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.

== Greek Pita Pockets for Lunch ==

Halve @whole wheat pitas{2}(halved) crosswise. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%oz}, a drizzle of olive oil, and as much remaining feta as you like; season with salt and pepper. Divide meatballs between 2 #reusable containers{}. Divide sour cream sauce between 2 more reusable containers. Pack pitas, cucumber, and sliced onion in 2 #zip-close bags{}. Just before eating, warm meatballs in #microwave{}. Stuff pitas with meatballs, cucumber, and onion; drizzle with sauce.

